body.description: Designed to save you time in the kitchen, Calphalon Classic Hard-Anodized Nonstick Cookware delivers cooking versatility every step of the way with an improved* easy-release surface. Featuring AquaShield nonstick technology, this cookware line performs like new 40% longer* for remarkable food release over and over again. Made with water-based nonstick and a hard-anodized exterior, it's dishwasher-safe for quick cleanup. Long stainless steel handles make lifting and moving easy and stay cool on the stovetop. This nonstick frying pan set is oven-safe up to 450 degrees F, so it can go from the stovetop into the oven for heating. Elevate your cooking experience with Calphalon Classic, and enjoy exceptional performance with endless possibilities. (*vs. previous generation of Calphalon Classic)

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Exceptionally Smooth Cooking Experience An essential for smooth, efficient cooking, Calphalon Classic Hard-Anodized Nonstick Cookware is designed with busy home cooks in mind. Made with water-based AquaShield nonstick technology, these pots and pans perform like new for 40% longer,* for remarkable food release. You can rely on the improved easy-release surface to help you achieve a flawless finish on everything from eggs to fish. Ideal for sautéing, searing, browning, and frying, this 2-piece fry pan set is a versatile addition to any kitchen. (*vs. previous generation of Calphalon Classic) Key Features Water-based AquaShield nonstick technology Dishwasher-safe Oven-safe up to 450 degrees F Long stainless steel handles Compatible with most stovetops, including gas, electric, and glass Includes one 8-inch pan and one 10-inch pan

Easy Release, Easy Cleanup Superior Nonstick Surface AquaShield technology delivers an exceptionally smooth surface for easy and enjoyable cooking. Dishwasher- and Oven-Safe Durable hard-anodized cookware is dishwasher-safe for time-saving cleanup, and oven-safe up to 450 degrees F. Stay-Cool Handle Long stainless steel handle is designed to stay comfortably cool on the stovetop.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Quality set of pans, well made, non stick, easy to clean, would recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Top Notch skillets, non stick dream
reviews.reviewText: Perfect skillets and truly non stick...if you are used to cooking stuff at a high heat on the burner, DON'T do it. No need to cook on high...maybe that is why some people complained that food stuck. Some of the photos that I saw in the 1* reviews had food stuck & looked as if the food was cooked way too high. I cook fried eggs, scrambled eggs, potatoes and rib eye steak and never once have I experienced sticking. I do know the instructions say NOT to use aresol sprays like Pam...they say only to use the pump type or mist type non stick products, so I do.The skillets are easy to hand wash (with soap & water) as well. I do not put my skillets in the dishwasher.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love the size and weight
reviews.reviewText: We love this pan. We had one for years but the finish was gone. It doesn't have the grip handle on the opposite side like my previous one and I will miss that. It cooks beautifully without being heavy. Great value.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I quit buying cheap non-stick cookware after my first Calphalon pan. This one is as good as the others I have. It heats fast and evenly, browns food nicely, and is easy to clean.I hesitate to call any non-stick pan "scratch resistant", but these are as good as any and better than most. With a little care they last many times longer cheaper non-sticks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Will last for years, IF you follow the instructions.
reviews.reviewText: The only reason I'm having to buy these pans, is because of my son-in-law. He has ruined my other pans by NOT FOLLOWING INSTRUCTIONS. These are the rules with any non-stick pan that you want to KEEP non-stick. 1) No high heat! These pans work exceedingly well at low and medium. Even pre-heating these pans on high will warp the metal and damage the non-stick coating. 2)HAND WASH ONLY! Automatic dishwasher detergents have caustic agents in them that will damage certain metals and will ruin non-stick coatings. 3) NO SPRAYS! Things like Pam have a propellent in them that will also damage the non-stick coating. 4) NO COLD WATER ON A HOT PAN! Who does that? I've seen him take a sizzling hot pan and run cold water right out of the faucet on it. Really? I'm sure that he does that to get the grease out, while the pan is still hot. But, doing so will warp the metal and ruin the non-stick coating. 5) NO METAL UTENSILS! Again, who does that? I've seen metal spoons, ladles, forks, spatulas and even KNIVES used on my pans. Don't do that. Just.....DON'T.Calphalon brand pans are some of the best on the market and will last YEARS if they are treated with care and respect. I have a full set of Calphalon pots and pans. I am very pleased with them and have full confidence that everything I cook in them is going to turn out great. Good purchase. Five stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Nice at first but they don’t last long
reviews.reviewText: They work great but longevity is an issue. I don’t even cook with them too often and the nonstick has scraped off quite quickly. I’m a little disappointed I didn’t even get a year out of them.

Great pan but this one has more rounded edges than flared out ones so it holds more water and so is not as good for searing as the old design. Still love using it to make omelettes and other stuff, easy to clean, and the heat distribution is excellent, I just wish I didn't scratch my old one =( it was my go to for yeeeears

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 7, 2023

reviews.reviewText: Llegaron 3 días antes de lo esperado, estoy En México City, super bien empacados y protegidos. Son de excelente calidad pesan, sin llegar a ser estorbosos. Si preparas alimentos sin aceite llegan a adherirse un poco pero con el paso de la cocción comienzan a despegarse solos. Si lo usas con cantidades pequeñas de aceite son una maravilla, nada se les pega. Hay que ser cuidadoso al lavarlos y no someterlos a choques de temperatura para mayor durabilidad del teflón. Excelente producto, altamente recomendado.
